\v 1 Peter, an apostle of Jesus Christ, to the chosen exiles\f +physical exiles or theological? cf. 2:11 where it has a more theological meaning - living the Christian life in a hostile environment; There were Gentile Christians in these areas, so the letter most likely is addressed to the elect of the church, not just Jews\f* of the Diaspora of Pontus, Galatia, Cappadocia, Asia and Bythinia,
\v 2 according to the foreknowledge\f +refer to Peter or exiles? Apostle or chosen? probably the chosen exiles, especially since he develops this foreknowledge with reference to the people in the book, and his apostleship is not a major theme sprinkling of blood: OT sacrifices, cf. Grudem - ongoing Christian experience, forgiveness when we fail foreknowledge: what is it?  subjective genitive\f* of God the Father in the sanctification of the Spirit into obedience and the sprinkling of the blood of Jesus Christ, grace to you and peace increasing \f +A, P, Opt., 3, s\f*.
